              "latency_ms": 6620.480291021522,
              "response": "When adding a new API endpoint, you should follow these coding standards:\n\n1. **File Structure**: Create the new API route in the appropriate directory, typically under `apps/web/src/app/api/[resource]/route.ts`.\n\n2. **Database Access**: Add any necessary database access logic in `lib/db/queries/`.\n\n3. **Validation**: Implement validation for the request body using Zod schemas.\n\n4. **Testing**: Write tests for the new endpoint in a corresponding `route.test.ts` file.\n\n5. **Linting and Type Checking**: After implementing the endpoint, run the following commands to ensure code quality:\n   - `pnpm lint`\n   - `pnpm type-check`\n   - `pnpm test`\n\n6. **Route Handler Pattern**: Ensure that your route handler:\n   - Authenticates the user (using `requireAuth()`).\n   - Validates input using the Zod schema.\n   - Delegates the business logic to a service or query.\n   - Returns a response, handling errors appropriately.\n\nBy adhering to these standards, you will maintain consistency and quality in the Snipara codebase.",
